&lt;p&gt;Moreover, one needs to remember a few things while buying a green home such as the LEED (Leadership in Energy and Environmental Design) rating, which is a globally-recognized system for certifying green buildings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But if one has a regular house then also later it can be modified into an eco-friendly home because the common factors that work in both the cases include energy efficiency, water conservation, preservation of natural resources, generating less waste and maintaining a healthy neighborhood.&lt;/p&gt;</content>
